{
  "stem": "21527.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now as I said, at that stage, there were 500 men and the-- and my uncle and my aunt and I.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My uncle straight away started pressing the Germans to construct some sort of a hospital and infirmary so that people could be treated properly.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The name of the camp was Warta Arbeitslager, which is a working camp.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was actually an ammunition factory.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the 500 men from the ghetto would go into this factory every morning and work.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there were Polish people who would come from the outside also to work in this camp.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When my aunt and uncle were searched, when we came to the previous camp, my aunt was able-- they-- all their precious belong-- even her wedding ring was taken off her finger, but she managed to hide a little diamond.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She actually sewed it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The dress which she was wearing, which she still had from home, had-- has four pockets with little bows on the pockets.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So she was able to sew inside the, the little bow, the diamond.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But when they knew that they would go through a search going out of the camp going into the new camp, my auntie took the diamond out and my uncle swallowed it.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He actually, actually swallowed it on two separate occasions.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he was lucky later to be able to go to the toilet and, and to find it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "When they go up to the camp in Czestochowa, they were able to sell this diamond to one of the Poles who came in every day.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And for the remainder of our stay in the camp, we were able to buy a little bit of extra bread, a little bit of extra nourishment, which the Poles brought, brought in as their lunches.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
